sar/sadf: [A_NET_ETCP]: Rename retrans/s field to retrseg/s

A_NET_ETCP report (displayed by "sar -n ETCP") has a column named
retrans/s. This name is also used in the A_NET_NFS report, which can be
confusing. So rename it to retrseg/s.
This field is also renamed in the output of sadf (PPC, DB and SVG output
formats).

sysstat-12.7.5

sysstat version 12.7.5 final packaging.
Changelog added.
spec file updated.

The sar command here includes two new metrics (pgprom/s et pgdem/s) so
that we can now track the number of pages promoted or demoted by the
system per second (that is to say, the number of pages migrated from
slow to fast, or from fast to slow, memory types).
Another metric (%vmeff) has also been removed from sar, as it was more a
kernel metric than a system one and it was wrongly calculated with
recent kernels.
You will also find various small fixes and improvements in this version.

Signed-off-by: Sebastien GODARD <sysstat@users.noreply.github.com>

Use correct encoding to produce hyphen-minus when rendering man pages

When a user searches a man page in e.g, less, when they search for -
less searches for U+002D HYPHEN MINUS.

As of groff 1.2, - renders out as U+2010 HYPHEN.

Therefore, it has become difficult to search for options in man pages.
This change switches man pages to use the escape sequence \- which
renders out as U+002D HYPHEN MINUS.

See: groff_man(7), <https://lwn.net/Articles/947941/>

sar: Add pgprom/s pgdem/s fields

Add the fields pgprom/s and pgdem/s so that we can track the promote
and demote metrics by using the sar command.

promotion: pgpromote_success
demotion: pgdemote_kswapd + pgdemote_direct + pgdemote_khugepaged

Below is an example where "pgprom/s" and "pgdem/s" are newly added
fields.

$ sar -B
